    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI don't know if anyone proposed this ever, but...\r\n\r\nWe have Insert, Visual, Normal modes.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n Imagine world where we can define our own modes:\r\nI.e. in LazyVim (god given)(cuz I'm lazy ;)) hit \\<leader\\>du DAP ui pops up, but every time we want to toggle breakpoint or whatever I have to \\<leader\\>db\\<leader\\>dc\\<leader\\>db\\<leader\\>dc\\<leader\\>db\\<leader\\>dC\\<leader\\>db\\<leader\\>db\\<leader\\>dc\\<leader\\>db...\r\nIt's exhausting. What if \\<leader\\>d switches nvim to \"Debug\" mode and we simply bbcbjjjCbb. Faster, simpler, nicer. To leave that mode we simply hit \\<Esc\\> ¯\\_(ツ)_/¯",
